386→                        <div id="content">Let $A(n)=\{a_0&#60;a_1&#60;\cdots\}$ be the sequence defined by $a_0=0$ and $a_1=n$, and for $k\geq 1$ define $a_{k+1}$ as the least positive integer such that there is no three-term arithmetic progression in $\{a_0,\ldots,a_{k+1}\}$.<br><br>Can the $a_k$ be explicitly determined? How fast do they grow?</div>
387→                        <div id="problem_id"><a href="/271">#271</a>: <a href="#cite-ErGr80-271" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('ErGr80','271'); return false;">[ErGr80,p.22]</a></div>
